commit d3cd74d331f23d7f654aff57da500a7280e85c95
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun Mar 29 08:35:14 2009 -0500

    core: add a wait_nointr() function and use {read,wait}_nointr() in cola.git
    
    cola.git's execute() method now uses {read,wait}_nointr() to handle the
    "interrupted system call" problem.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 0452fe48cfe19f85c20303d02a3077efdbd08a6e
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun Mar 29 02:52:08 2009 -0500

    refactor: change various modules to use core.{read,write}_nointr
    
    OSX and other systems can interrupt us in the middle of a system call so
    wrap all read/write calls with an automatic retry loop.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 19964a0ec15fa30c179f6744ed653739735af9b6
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun Mar 29 02:49:00 2009 -0500

    core: add read/write_nointr helper functions
    
    read/write_nointr automatically retries interrupted system calls.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit 4b12880b731c923fd9d78d679f7e7a3126ce395b
Author: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun Mar 29 02:00:24 2009 -0500

    git: catch OSError in addition to IOError in the execute() method
    
    Popen.wait() can throw OSError errno.EINTR, so catch it and retry the syscall.
    
    Signed-off-by: David Aguilar <davvid@gmail.com>

commit d04e6d5a0556bb807572dda13ed3c7348f0d8a87
